TITLE: Adding an Item to an Existing Item Group in Fabric
DESCRIPTION: Updates the initialize method to add the registered item to the Ingredients item group using Fabric API's ItemGroupEvents. This makes the item appear in the creative inventory under that tab.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/versions/1.21/develop/items/first-item.md#2025-04-05_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public class ModItems {
    // Register Method
    public static <T extends Item> T register(T item, String name) {
        return Registry.register(Registries.ITEM, new Identifier("mod_id", name), item);
    }

    // Item Instances
    public static final Item SUSPICIOUS_SUBSTANCE = register(new Item(new FabricItemSettings()), "suspicious_substance");

    // Initialize Method (Called from the Mod Initializer)
    public static void initialize() {
        // Add the item to the Ingredients item group
        ItemGroupEvents.modifyEntriesEvent(ItemGroups.INGREDIENTS).register(content -> {
            content.add(SUSPICIOUS_SUBSTANCE);
        });
    }
}
```

