TITLE: Using Advanced Sound System in Network Handling
DESCRIPTION: Example of using the DynamicSoundManager to start and stop custom dynamic SoundInstances in response to network events.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/translated/it_it/develop/sounds/dynamic-sounds.md#2025-04-05_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public class ReceiveS2C {
    public static void onEngineStart(EngineBlockEntity engine) {
        DynamicSoundManager.getInstance().playSound(
            new EngineSoundInstance(
                ModSounds.ENGINE_RUNNING,
                engine,
                () -> DynamicSoundManager.getInstance().stopSound(engine.getSoundInstance())
            )
        );
    }

    public static void onEngineStop(EngineBlockEntity engine) {
        if (engine.getSoundInstance() != null) {
            engine.getSoundInstance().stopPlaying();
        }
    }
}
```

