TITLE: Modifying Loot Tables with LootTableEvents in Java
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to use LootTableEvents.MODIFY to add eggs to the iron ore block's loot table. It demonstrates detecting loot table loading and adding items to existing loot tables.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/versions/1.20.4/translated/es_es/develop/events.md#2025-04-05_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
LootTableEvents.MODIFY.register((resourceManager, lootManager, id, tableBuilder, source) -> {
    if (source.isBuiltin() && Blocks.IRON_ORE.getLootTableId().equals(id)) {
        LootPool.Builder poolBuilder = LootPool.builder()
                .rolls(ConstantLootNumberProvider.create(1))
                .with(ItemEntry.builder(Items.EGG)
                        .apply(SetCountLootFunction.builder(UniformLootNumberProvider.create(1.0f, 2.0f))));
        tableBuilder.pool(poolBuilder);
    }
});
```

