TITLE: Creating a Custom Widget by Extending ClickableWidget in Java
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a custom widget by extending the ClickableWidget class. It sets up position, size, text, and implements rendering functionality with custom background and text drawing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/versions/1.21/develop/rendering/gui/custom-widgets.md#2025-04-05_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
package com.example.docs.rendering.screens;

import net.minecraft.client.gui.DrawContext;
import net.minecraft.client.gui.widget.ClickableWidget;
import net.minecraft.text.Text;

public class CustomWidget extends ClickableWidget {
    private static final int NORMAL_COLOR = 0xFF000000;
    private static final int HOVERED_COLOR = 0xFF333333;

    public CustomWidget(int x, int y, int width, int height, Text message) {
        super(x, y, width, height, message);
    }

    @Override
    protected void renderWidget(DrawContext context, int mouseX, int mouseY, float delta) {
        int backgroundColor = isHovered() ? HOVERED_COLOR : NORMAL_COLOR;

        // Render background
        context.fill(getX(), getY(), getX() + width, getY() + height, backgroundColor);

        // Render text
        int textColor = 0xFFFFFFFF; // White
        context.drawCenteredTextWithShadow(
            textRenderer, getMessage(), getX() + width / 2, getY() + (height - textRenderer.fontHeight) / 2, textColor
        );
    }
}
```

