TITLE: Handling Received Packets on the Client in Java
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to register a global receiver for handling packets sent from the server to the client. It creates a lightning entity at the specified position when the packet is received.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/develop/networking.md#2025-04-05_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
ClientPlayNetworking.registerGlobalReceiver(SummonLightningS2CPayload.TYPE, (payload, context) -> {
    BlockPos pos = payload.pos();
    context.client().execute(() -> {
        LightningEntity lightningEntity = EntityType.LIGHTNING_BOLT.create(context.client().world);
        if (lightningEntity != null) {
            lightningEntity.refreshPositionAfterTeleport(pos.getX(), pos.getY(), pos.getZ());
            context.client().world.addEntity(lightningEntity.getId(), lightningEntity);
        }
    });
});
```

