TITLE: Registering Attack Block Callback in Java
DESCRIPTION: This code registers an AttackBlockCallback that damages a player when they hit blocks that don't drop an item without tools.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/versions/1.20.4/translated/it_it/develop/events.md#2025-04-05_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
AttackBlockCallback.EVENT.register((player, world, hand, pos, direction) -> {
    BlockState state = world.getBlockState(pos);
    Block block = state.getBlock();
    if (world.getBlockEntity(pos) == null
        && state.getHardness(world, pos) != -1.0F
        && !(player.getStackInHand(hand).isEmpty() && block.drops(state).isEmpty())) {
        player.damage(world.getDamageSources().generic(), 0.5F);
    }
    return ActionResult.PASS;
});
```

