TITLE: Implementing a Lightning Tater Item with Networking
DESCRIPTION: This code implements a custom item that sends packets to clients when used. It demonstrates proper server-side detection and player lookup to only send packets to relevant players who should receive the notification.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/translated/de_de/develop/networking.md#2025-04-05_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public class LightningTaterItem extends Item {
    public LightningTaterItem(Settings settings) {
        super(settings);
    }

    @Override
    public TypedActionResult<ItemStack> use(World world, PlayerEntity user, Hand hand) {
        ItemStack stack = user.getStackInHand(hand);

        // Only send packets if this is running on the server
        if (world.isClient) {
            return TypedActionResult.pass(stack);
        }

        SummonLightningS2CPayload payload = new SummonLightningS2CPayload(user.getBlockPos());

        // Send a packet to all players tracking the user
        for (ServerPlayerEntity player : PlayerLookup.tracking(world, user.getBlockPos())) {
            ServerPlayNetworking.send(player, payload);
        }

        return TypedActionResult.success(stack);
    }
}
```

