TITLE: Implementing Tick Method for Dynamic Sound Behavior in Java
DESCRIPTION: Implements the tick method to apply different values and behaviors based on the current tick of the SoundInstance.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/versions/1.21/develop/sounds/dynamic-sounds.md#2025-04-05_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
@Override
public void tick() {
    this.ticksExisted++;
    this.ticksPlayed++;

    if (this.source.shouldStopSound()) {
        if (this.transitionState != TransitionState.END) {
            this.transitionState = TransitionState.END;
            this.ticksPlayed = 0;
        }
    }

    if (this.transitionState == TransitionState.START && this.ticksPlayed >= this.startTicks) {
        this.transitionState = TransitionState.MIDDLE;
        this.ticksPlayed = 0;
    } else if (this.transitionState == TransitionState.END && this.ticksPlayed >= this.endTicks) {
        this.finished = true;
        this.finishCallback.accept(this);
    }
}
```

