TITLE: Creating a DynamicSoundSource Interface for Advanced Sound Systems
DESCRIPTION: Defines an interface that provides necessary data for dynamic sound sources. This abstraction allows the sound system to work with different types of entities and block entities as sound sources.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/develop/sounds/dynamic-sounds.md#2025-04-05_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public interface DynamicSoundSource {
    /**
     * Returns the block position of this sound source.
     * <p>
     * The sound will use this position as the default position to play from,
     * but it can be overridden in specific sound implementations.
     *
     * @return The position of this sound source
     */
    BlockPos getBlockPos();

    /**
     * Returns the identifier of this sound source.
     * <p>
     * This is used to uniquely identify this sound source,
     * so sounds can be correctly mapped to their sources.
     *
     * @return The identifier of this sound source
     */
    Identifier getSoundId();

    /**
     * Returns the current state of this sound source.
     * <p>
     * Can be used to determine if a sound should be playing or not.
     *
     * @return The current state
     */
    TransitionState getSoundState();

    /**
     * Returns the volume multiplier of this sound source.
     * <p>
     * Can be used to adjust the volume of sounds based on
     * specific properties of the sound source.
     *
     * @return The volume multiplier
     */
    float getVolumeMultiplier();

    /**
     * Returns the pitch multiplier of this sound source.
     * <p>
     * Can be used to adjust the pitch of sounds based on
     * specific properties of the sound source.
     *
     * @return The pitch multiplier
     */
    float getPitchMultiplier();
}
```

