TITLE: Registering an Attack Block Event Callback in Java
DESCRIPTION: An example that registers an AttackBlockCallback to damage the player when they hit blocks that don't drop an item when hand-mined. The callback returns SUCCESS to indicate the action was handled.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/develop/events.md#2025-04-05_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
// Register the callback in our mod initializer class
AttackBlockCallback.EVENT.register((player, world, hand, pos, direction) -> {
    BlockState state = world.getBlockState(pos);
    ItemStack tool = player.getStackInHand(hand);

    // Check if the block doesn't drop anything when mined by hand
    if (!state.getDroppedStacks(new LootContext.Builder((ServerWorld) world)).isEmpty() || !tool.isEmpty()) {
        return ActionResult.PASS; // Let the game continue with the normal mining behavior
    }

    // Otherwise, hurt the player
    player.damage(world.getDamageSources().generic(), 1.0F);
    return ActionResult.SUCCESS; // We've handled this action
});
```

