TITLE: Implementing Sound Modulation Methods in AbstractDynamicSoundInstance in Java
DESCRIPTION: Provides utility methods for calculating dynamic volume and pitch transitions based on the current state. These methods enable smooth transitions between sound states using linear interpolation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/versions/1.21/translated/it_it/develop/sounds/dynamic-sounds.md#2025-04-05_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
    protected abstract void applyModulations();

    protected float getTransitionVolume() {
        return switch (this.state) {
            case INTRO -> {
                float progress = (float) this.loopTicks / this.introTicks;
                yield MathHelper.lerp(progress, this.minVolume, this.maxVolume);
            }
            case LOOP -> this.maxVolume;
            case OUTRO -> {
                float progress = (float) this.loopTicks / this.outroTicks;
                yield MathHelper.lerp(progress, this.maxVolume, this.minVolume);
            }
        };
    }

    protected float normalizeAndLerpValue(float value, float normalizedMin, float normalizedMax) {
        value = MathHelper.clamp(value, 0.0F, 1.0F);
        return MathHelper.lerp(value, normalizedMin, normalizedMax);
    }
```

