TITLE: TransitionState Enum for Sound Transition Management
DESCRIPTION: Enum defining the possible states of a dynamic sound: STARTING, RUNNING, and ENDING. Includes utility methods for serialization and lookup by identifier for networking purposes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/versions/1.21/develop/sounds/dynamic-sounds.md#2025-04-05_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public enum TransitionState {
    STARTING(new Identifier("example", "starting")),
    RUNNING(new Identifier("example", "running")),
    ENDING(new Identifier("example", "ending"));

    private final Identifier id;

    TransitionState(Identifier id) {
        this.id = id;
    }

    public Identifier getId() {
        return id;
    }

    /**
     * Find a transition state by its identifier.
     * Useful when sending/receiving data over the network.
     */
    public static TransitionState fromId(Identifier id) {
        for (TransitionState state : values()) {
            if (state.id.equals(id)) {
                return state;
            }
        }
        return RUNNING; // Default fallback
    }
}
```

