TITLE: Adding a Block Item to Custom Item Group in Java
DESCRIPTION: Erweitert die Blockregistrierung, um das Block-Item einer benutzerdefinierten Itemgruppe hinzuzufgen, indem ein ItemGroupEvents.ModifyEntries-Event-Handler verwendet wird.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/translated/de_de/develop/blocks/first-block.md#2025-04-05_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
// Register method for blocks, with a boolean to determine if an item should be registered for the block
private static <T extends Block> T register(String id, T block, boolean shouldRegisterItem) {
    // Register our block to the "BLOCK" registry
    Registry.register(Registries.BLOCK, new Identifier("fabric-docs-reference", id), block);

    // If shouldRegisterItem is true, also register a BlockItem for the block.
    if (shouldRegisterItem) {
        BlockItem blockItem = new BlockItem(block, new FabricItemSettings());
        // Register the BlockItem to the "ITEM" registry
        Registry.register(Registries.ITEM, new Identifier("fabric-docs-reference", id), blockItem);

        // Add the BlockItem to our custom item group
        // This callback will run when the item group is being populated
        ItemGroupEvents.modifyEntriesEvent(ModItemGroups.ITEM_GROUP).register(content -> {
            // Add the item to the item group
            content.add(blockItem);
        });
    }

    return block;
}
```

