TITLE: Extending StatusEffect Class for Custom Effect Implementation in Java
DESCRIPTION: Creates a custom 'Tater' status effect by extending the StatusEffect class. This effect gives the player one experience point per game tick when applied. The implementation includes setting the effect type (beneficial) and color.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/versions/1.20.4/translated/de_de/develop/entities/effects.md#2025-04-05_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public class TaterEffect extends StatusEffect {
    public TaterEffect() {
        // true = beneficial, 0x91D4FF is a light blue color for the effect
        super(StatusEffectCategory.BENEFICIAL, 0x91D4FF);
    }

    @Override
    public boolean canApplyUpdateEffect(int duration, int amplifier) {
        // This method determines how often the effect should apply the effect logic
        // For our tater effect, we want it to apply every tick
        return true;
    }

    @Override
    public void applyUpdateEffect(LivingEntity entity, int amplifier) {
        // This is where the effect logic is applied each tick
        // For our tater effect, we want to give the player one experience point every tick
        if (entity instanceof PlayerEntity) {
            ((PlayerEntity) entity).addExperience(1);
        }
    }
}
```

