TITLE: Implementing Scaling Animation with MatrixStack in Fabric
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to create a scaling animation effect for a diamond model using MatrixStack to apply transformations based on time. It properly manages the matrix stack by pushing before transformations and popping afterward.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/versions/1.20.4/develop/rendering/basic-concepts.md#2025-04-05_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
@Override
public void render(MatrixStack matrices, VertexConsumerProvider vertexConsumers, double x, double y, double tickDelta) {
    float scale = 0.5f + (float) Math.sin(tickDelta / 8) * 0.25f;

    // Push the matrix stack and translate to the correct position
    matrices.push();
    matrices.translate(x, y, 0);
    matrices.scale(scale, scale, scale);

    // Get the transformation matrix from the matrix stack
    Matrix4f matrix = matrices.peek().getPositionMatrix();

    // Render the diamond
    this.renderDiamond(matrix, vertexConsumers.getBuffer(RenderLayer.getLines()));

    // Pop the matrix stack
    matrices.pop();
}
```

