TITLE: Implementing use() Method for LightningStick
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of the use() method that summons lightning 10 blocks in front of the player when the item is used, with a cooldown to prevent spam.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/translated/zh_cn/develop/items/custom-item-interactions.md#2025-04-05_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
@Override
public TypedActionResult<ItemStack> use(World world, PlayerEntity user, Hand hand) {
    if (!world.isClient()) {
        // Set a cooldown for the item (20 ticks, or 1 second)
        user.getItemCooldownManager().set(this, 20);

        // Get the rotation of the player
        float pitch = user.getPitch();
        float yaw = user.getYaw();

        // Get the position where the lightning should be summoned
        // In this case, 10 blocks in front of the player
        double x = user.getX() - Math.sin(Math.toRadians(yaw)) * 10;
        double z = user.getZ() + Math.cos(Math.toRadians(yaw)) * 10;

        // Spawn the lightning bolt
        LightningEntity lightningEntity = new LightningEntity(EntityType.LIGHTNING_BOLT, world);
        lightningEntity.setPosition(x, user.getY(), z);
        world.spawnEntity(lightningEntity);
    }

    return TypedActionResult.success(user.getStackInHand(hand));
}
```

