TITLE: Initializing Block Registration Method in Java
DESCRIPTION: A utility method for registering blocks and their respective block items in Minecraft. The method handles both block registration and creates a BlockItem when specified.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/develop/blocks/first-block.md#2025-04-05_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
private static <T extends Block> T register(String path, T block, boolean shouldRegisterItem) {
    // We register the block with the ID constructed from our mod ID and the provided path
    Identifier id = new Identifier(FabricDocsReference.MOD_ID, path);
    // We register the block with the identifier we just constructed
    Registry.register(Registries.BLOCK, id, block);

    // If shouldRegisterItem is true, we also create and register a BlockItem
    if (shouldRegisterItem) {
        BlockItem item = new BlockItem(block, new Item.Settings());
        // Then we register the BlockItem
        Registry.register(Registries.ITEM, id, item);
    }

    // Finally, we return the block so we can store it somewhere
    return block;
}
```

