TITLE: Implementing Custom EngineSoundInstance in Java
DESCRIPTION: Creates a concrete implementation of AbstractDynamicSoundInstance for an engine sound. This implementation determines playback conditions and applies specific sound modulations based on the engine's stress level.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/versions/1.21/translated/it_it/develop/sounds/dynamic-sounds.md#2025-04-05_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
package com.example.docs.sound.instance;

import com.example.docs.sound.AbstractDynamicSoundInstance;
import net.minecraft.sound.SoundCategory;
import net.minecraft.util.Identifier;

public class EngineSoundInstance extends AbstractDynamicSoundInstance {
    public EngineSoundInstance(Identifier id, DynamicSoundSource source, SoundInstanceCallback callback, Object callbackId) {
        super(id, SoundCategory.BLOCKS, source, callback, callbackId);
    }

    @Override
    protected boolean shouldContinuePlaying() {
        // The engine's running state determines if the sound should continue
        return this.source.isActive();
    }

    @Override
    protected void applyModulations() {
        // Apply volume based on transition state
        this.volume = getTransitionVolume();

        // Apply pitch based on engine stress
        float engineStress = this.source.getModulationValue();
        this.pitch = normalizeAndLerpValue(engineStress, this.getMinPitch(), this.getMaxPitch());
    }
}
```

