TITLE: Executing Command with Custom Suggestions in Java
DESCRIPTION: This code shows the execution logic for a command using custom player suggestions. It retrieves the player argument and sends a message to the command source with the selected player name.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/versions/1.21/develop/commands/suggestions.md#2025-04-05_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
private static int executeCommandWithCustomSuggestions(CommandContext<ServerCommandSource> context) throws CommandSyntaxException {
    ServerCommandSource source = context.getSource();

