TITLE: Implementing Tick Logic for AbstractDynamicSoundInstance in Java
DESCRIPTION: Manages the sound instance's state transitions and duration tracking on each tick. This method handles the progression through intro, loop, and outro phases, and signals completion when finished.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/versions/1.21/translated/it_it/develop/sounds/dynamic-sounds.md#2025-04-05_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
    public void tick() {
        // Increment counters
        this.ticks++;
        this.loopTicks++;

        // Update sound position based on source
        Vec3d pos = this.source.getPos();
        this.x = pos.x;
        this.y = pos.y;
        this.z = pos.z;

        if (this.done) {
            return;
        }

        if (!shouldContinuePlaying()) {
            if (this.state != TransitionState.OUTRO) {
                this.state = TransitionState.OUTRO;
                this.loopTicks = 0;
            }
        }

        switch (this.state) {
            case INTRO -> {
                if (this.loopTicks >= this.introTicks) {
                    this.state = TransitionState.LOOP;
                    this.loopTicks = 0;
                }
            }
            case OUTRO -> {
                if (this.loopTicks >= this.outroTicks) {
                    this.done = true;
                    this.callback.onFinished(this.id);
                }
            }
        }

        // Apply dynamic volume and pitch modulations
        applyModulations();
    }
```

