TITLE: Implementing a Block Break Notification with Mixin in Java
DESCRIPTION: Sets up a mod entrypoint that tracks the tools players use to break blocks. This implementation uses a HashMap to store player-tool mappings and demonstrates how to track player actions for custom advancement criteria.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/develop/data-generation/advancements.md#2025-04-05_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public class FabricDocsReferenceDatagenAdvancement implements ModInitializer {
    private static final HashMap<UUID, Item> PLAYER_TOOLS = new HashMap<>();

    @Override
    public void onInitialize() {
        ServerBlockBreakEvents.AFTER.register((world, player, pos, state, blockEntity) -> {
            if (PLAYER_TOOLS.containsKey(player.getUuid())) {
                Item item = PLAYER_TOOLS.get(player.getUuid());
                // Test prints to show our custom criterion working
                player.sendMessage(Text.of("You broke a block with " + item.getTranslationKey()));
            }
        });

        ServerPlayConnectionEvents.JOIN.register((handler, sender, server) -> 
            PLAYER_TOOLS.put(handler.player.getUuid(), Items.AIR));

        UseBlockCallback.EVENT.register((player, world, hand, hitResult) -> {
            if (player instanceof ServerPlayerEntity && !world.isClient() && hand == Hand.MAIN_HAND) {
                PLAYER_TOOLS.put(player.getUuid(), player.getMainHandStack().getItem());
            }
            return ActionResult.PASS;
        });
    }
```

