TITLE: Implementing Custom EngineSoundInstance in Java
DESCRIPTION: Extends AbstractDynamicSoundInstance to create a specific sound instance for an engine. It defines conditions for stopping the sound and applies custom sound modulations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/develop/sounds/dynamic-sounds.md#2025-04-05_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public class EngineSoundInstance extends AbstractDynamicSoundInstance {
    private final BlockPos pos;

    public EngineSoundInstance(World world, BlockPos pos) {
        super(
                new BlockEntityDynamicSoundSource(world, pos),
                SoundEvents.BLOCK_BEACON_AMBIENT,
                SoundCategory.BLOCKS,
                DynamicSoundManager.getInstance()::onSoundFinished
        );
        this.pos = pos;
    }

    @Override
    protected void applyModulations() {
        if (this.soundSource.getStress() <= 0) {
            this.stopSound();
        }
    }

    @Override
    public boolean shouldAlwaysPlay() {
        return true;
    }

    @Override
    public boolean canPlay() {
        return super.canPlay() && !this.soundSource.getWorld().getBlockState(this.pos).isAir();
    }
}
```

