TITLE: Creating Advancements with Parameterized Criteria in Java
DESCRIPTION: Creates advancements that use the parameterized criterion, requiring different numbers of tool uses. This demonstrates how to create tiered advancements with custom requirements.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/develop/data-generation/advancements.md#2025-04-05_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
private void generateParameterizedCriterionAdvancement(Consumer<Advancement> consumer) {
    var useToolFiveTimesDisplay = new AdvancementDisplay(
            Items.GOLDEN_PICKAXE.getDefaultStack(),
            Text.translatable("advancements.fabric-docs-reference.use_tool_5_times.title"),
            Text.translatable("advancements.fabric-docs-reference.use_tool_5_times.description"),
            new Identifier("textures/gui/advancements/backgrounds/adventure.png"),
            AdvancementFrame.TASK,
            true,
            true,
            false
    );

    Advancement useToolFiveTimes = Advancement.Builder.create()
            .display(useToolFiveTimesDisplay)
            .criterion("used_tool_5_times", ModCriteria.PARAMETERIZED_USE_TOOL.criterionConditionsFactory(
                    new ParameterizedUseToolCriterion.Conditions(ContextAwarePredicate.createEmpty(), 5)))
            .build(consumer, "fabric-docs-reference:use_tool_5_times");

    var useToolTenTimesDisplay = new AdvancementDisplay(
            Items.DIAMOND_PICKAXE.getDefaultStack(),
            Text.translatable("advancements.fabric-docs-reference.use_tool_10_times.title"),
            Text.translatable("advancements.fabric-docs-reference.use_tool_10_times.description"),
            new Identifier("textures/gui/advancements/backgrounds/adventure.png"),
            AdvancementFrame.CHALLENGE,
            true,
            true,
            false
    );

    Advancement useToolTenTimes = Advancement.Builder.create()
            .display(useToolTenTimesDisplay)
            .parent(useToolFiveTimes)
            .criterion("used_tool_10_times", ModCriteria.PARAMETERIZED_USE_TOOL.criterionConditionsFactory(
                    new ParameterizedUseToolCriterion.Conditions(ContextAwarePredicate.createEmpty(), 10)))
            .rewards(AdvancementRewards.Builder.experience(500).build())
            .build(consumer, "fabric-docs-reference:use_tool_10_times");
}
```

