TITLE: Implementing a TransitionState Enum for Sound Transitions
DESCRIPTION: Defines an enum for managing sound transition states (starting, running, ending). This helps create smooth volume transitions when starting or stopping sounds rather than abrupt changes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-docs/blob/main/develop/sounds/dynamic-sounds.md#2025-04-05_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public enum TransitionState {
    STARTING(new Identifier(FabricDocs.MOD_ID, "starting")),
    RUNNING(new Identifier(FabricDocs.MOD_ID, "running")),
    ENDING(new Identifier(FabricDocs.MOD_ID, "ending"));

    private final Identifier id;

    TransitionState(Identifier id) {
        this.id = id;
    }

    public Identifier getId() {
        return id;
    }

    public static TransitionState fromId(Identifier id) {
        for (TransitionState state : values()) {
            if (state.id.equals(id)) {
                return state;
            }
        }
        return ENDING;
    }
}
```

